column1: Baby Barnaby's////2. For their hash browns
column2: they use the standard cube shape potato...HOWEVER
column3: they fry it. And that my friend was pretty gangsta. I don't like most hash browns outside of the McDonald-Burger-king-fried type. And when I heard that they had the cube shaped-seasoned ones
column4: I was a bit skeptical b/c they are just chopped up and sauteed. But yeah
column5: these were good b/c it's fried. Who doesn't love fried food?
